      "Full Stack Engineer\nBankroll U\nTucson, AZ • Remote\n\n\n1-Click Apply\n\n\n$120K - $145K/yr\n\nFull-time\n\nMedical, Dental, Vision, PTO\n\nPosted 10 hours ago\n\nBe Seen First\n\nAfter you apply to this job, you can share why you’re interested to jump to the top of the candidate list.\n\nJob description\nFull-Stack Software Engineer | Sports-Tech Startup | Contract-to-Hire\n\nWe're a fast-growing sports-tech startup building an innovative platform that helps players learn sports betting strategy through live-market simulated experiences. We're looking for a versatile full-stack engineer who thrives in a dynamic startup environment and wants to make a significant impact on our product from day one.\n\n \n\nAbout the Role\n\nYou'll join a lean, focused engineering team working across our entire technology stack - from database architecture to frontend experiences on web and mobile. This is a contract-to-hire position with a 1-2 month evaluation period at a competitive hourly rate ($70-80/hr), giving both sides confidence before transitioning to a full-time salaried role ($130K-$145K).\n\nThis isn't just another engineering job - it's an opportunity to be a foundational member of a growing company. You'll have real ownership over technical decisions, work directly with leadership, and help shape both our product and our engineering culture as we scale.\n\nDuring the initial contract period, you'll work on diverse projects across our stack to demonstrate your abilities and find your rhythm with the team. We're looking for someone who can independently debug issues across all layers of the application and contribute meaningfully from day one.\n\n \n\nWhat You'll Work With\n\nBackend: NestJS and Express (Node.js/TypeScript), PostgreSQL, Redis/Redis Queues\nFrontend: React (web), React Native (mobile)\nInfrastructure: Google Cloud Platform (AWS experience also valuable)\nReal-time data systems serving live sportsbook lines and user interactions\n \n\nRequired Experience\n\nStrong proficiency in TypeScript and modern JavaScript\nProduction experience with PostgreSQL and writing efficient SQL queries\nProduction experience with at least one modern Node.js backend framework (NestJS strongly preferred; Express acceptable)\nFrontend development with React (React Native experience highly preferred but strong React developers willing to learn React Native will be considered)\nExperience working with real-time data applications or systems requiring live updates\nComfortable deploying, monitoring, and troubleshooting production applications on Google Cloud Platform (or AWS with willingness to learn GCP)\nExperience responding to production incidents and debugging issues under pressure - you'll share on-call rotation with our lead engineer and need to independently triage and resolve issues\nProven debugging skills across the full stack - from database queries to UI rendering\nExcellent written communication skills for async collaboration with distributed team members\nComfort working independently and taking ownership of features end-to-end\n \n\nNon-Technical Skills\n\nBeyond technical skills, we need someone who:\n\nTakes initiative within agreed-upon priorities - proactively identifies solutions and unblocks themselves\nIs comfortable with ambiguity and changing requirements as our product evolves\nValues building things quickly while maintaining quality over perfection\nSees problems as puzzles to solve rather than blockers\nIs excited about the startup journey - the wins, the challenges, and everything in between\n \n\nNice to Have\n\nUnderstanding of sports and sports betting concepts\nExperience with Redis and message queues\nImproving CI/CD pipelines and development workflows\nExperience with or willingness to learn automated testing practices\nMobile development experience (native Swift/Kotlin and/or React Native)\n \n\nWhat We Offer\n\nGrowth opportunity: Be an early engineering hire with significant influence on technical direction and team building\nReal ownership: You'll help define what gets built and how\nDirect impact: Your work directly affects user experience and company success; you'll see the results of your code in production quickly\nLearn and grow: Work across the entire stack and gain experience in areas you want to develop\nFlexible environment: Remote-friendly with async-first communication and trust in how you manage your time\nStartup culture: Small team means your voice matters, less bureaucracy, and faster decision-making\n \n\nCompensation & Structure\n\nContract period: 1-2 months at $70/hour (based on experience)\nFull-time salary after conversion: $120K-$145K annually\nExpected timeline: We anticipate conversion to full-time salaried employee after 4-8 weeks, contingent on mutual fit\nEvaluation criteria: During the contract period, we'll assess your work across our stack, communication style, and overall team fit. We'll have clear checkpoints so you know where you stand.\n \n\nAbout Our Team\n\nYou'll be working closely with our lead engineer and collaborating with a contracted mobile developer. We value clear communication, initiative, and the ability to balance moving quickly with building sustainable solutions. Our product requirements evolve as we add new sports and features, so adaptability is essential.\n\n \n\nLocation & Hours\n\nRemote (US-based preferred) with core overlap during US business hours.\n\n \n\nTo Apply\n\nPlease include:\n\nYour resume highlighting relevant full-stack experience\nA brief note (3-4 sentences) about why you're interested in joining an early-stage sports-tech startup\nLinks to any public code samples, GitHub profile, or projects you're proud of\nCompany Description\nBankroll U is a cutting-edge sports betting platform that helps users build professional betting skills without risking real money. Through bankroll challenges and structured progression, users can qualify to earn real cash rewards based on performance. Our mission is to develop sharp, disciplined bettors by combining education, simulation, and community.",
