      "Sr Software Engineer\nConnection\nMiami, FL • Remote\n\n\n1-Click Apply\n\n\n$175K - $190K/yr\n\nFull-time\n\nMedical, Dental, Vision, Life, Retirement, PTO\n\nPosted 18 days ago\n\nBe Seen First\n\nAfter you apply to this job, you can share why you’re interested to jump to the top of the candidate list.\n\nJob description\nConnection has a fantastic opportunity through our Technical Staffing division for a Sr. Software Engineer to work remotely in the CST and EST time zones only. Great opportunity to work Fully remote (CST and EST time zones only) Flexible Paid Time Off, Company-paid holidays, Comprehensive insurance coverage (medical, dental, vision, short-term & long-term disability, life, accident), 401(k) plan, Paid parental leave.\n\nThis role supports an innovative SaaS organization delivering AI-powered underwriting, data intelligence, and intelligent document processing solutions to commercial Property & Casualty (P&C) insurance carriers, MGAs, brokers, and reinsurers. The platform enables insurers to streamline submission-to-quote workflows, improve decision accuracy, reduce manual processes, and enhance customer experience through advanced AI-driven decisioning.\n\nWe are seeking a Staff / Senior Software Engineer who operates with an ownership mindset. This is a highly autonomous individual contributor role for someone who thrives in fast-paced, high-growth environments and can identify, architect, and deliver impactful solutions end-to-end.\n\n \n\nThe ideal candidate demonstrates strong technical judgment, balances speed with scalability, and brings a refined sense of software craftsmanship — understanding when to build for scale and when to prioritize simplicity. You will own entire workstreams, influence architecture, and contribute to a high-performing engineering culture.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n \n\nOperate with a high degree of autonomy — identify high-impact opportunities and execute without requiring fully defined specifications.\nArchitect and deliver scalable, AI-driven features including autonomous workflows, intelligent assistants, and advanced decisioning capabilities.\nDesign clean abstractions, intuitive APIs, and maintain high-quality, type-safe code standards.\nDevelop across the full stack — database, APIs, and modern frontend frameworks.\nWrite maintainable, production-grade TypeScript code.\nImplement modern React and Next.js patterns focused on performance, scalability, and user experience.\nEnhance and maintain a modern developer experience and technology stack.\nCollaborate closely with product and engineering teams to shape technical direction.\nMentor peers through architectural guidance, code reviews, and engineering best practices.\nContribute to CI/CD pipelines, automated testing strategies, observability, and performance optimization.\n \n\nWhat You Bring\n\nProven success in high-growth, ambiguous, or startup environments.\nStrong hands-on experience building and deploying AI-powered applications to production.\nDeep understanding of large language models (LLMs), agentic frameworks, and real-world AI implementation challenges.\nStrong architectural judgment and ability to make sound technical trade-offs.\nLeadership through influence — raising the engineering bar through quality and mentorship.\n \n\nRequired Experience\n\n10+ years of professional experience in full-stack or frontend engineering.\nAdvanced proficiency in TypeScript and modern React.\nExperience working with AI tooling such as LangChain, OpenAI APIs, Anthropic APIs, or custom agentic workflows.\nHands-on experience with Next.js App Router (server components, streaming, caching, layouts).\nStrong background building complex, data-heavy user interfaces.\nExperience with Tailwind CSS and modern component libraries (e.g., shadcn/ui, Mantine, or similar).\nExperience with type-safe API frameworks such as tRPC or equivalent.\nSolid understanding of frontend performance optimization, state management, and accessibility standards.\nExperience working within SaaS platforms or startup environments.\nStrong system design skills and commitment to writing clean, scalable, maintainable code.\nExcellent communication skills and ability to work independently.\n \n\nBenefits & Compensation\n\nFully remote (CST and EST time zones only)\nFlexible Paid Time Off\nCompany-paid holidays\nComprehensive insurance coverage (medical, dental, vision, short-term & long-term disability, life, accident)\n401(k) plan\nPaid parental leave\n“Because of the possibility for fraudulent job postings on many popular job boards, please be advised that Connection will never offer a position of employment without a complete interview process, communication with a live person, and a signed offer letter.”\n\n“Applicants must be authorized to work for any employer in the U.S. We are unable to sponsor or take over sponsorship of an employment visa at this time.”",
