      "iOS App Developer\nat FGS Global (View all jobs)\nNew York, New York, United States\nAbout the Role \n\nWe're looking for an experienced iOS developer to build mobile capabilities for our internal AI platform. You'll own native iOS development, working closely with our backend engineering team to deliver high-quality mobile experiences for our consultant users across the firm. \n\nThis is a hands-on technical role with significant autonomy. You'll be responsible for the entire iOS codebase, from architecture decisions to implementation to enterprise deployment. We're not building prototypes—we're scaling proven capabilities that consultants rely on daily for high-stakes client work. \n\nWhat You'll Build \n\nYou'll develop mobile-first features that extend our AI platform beyond the desktop, bringing intelligent assistance to consultants wherever they work. The specific roadmap will evolve based on user needs, but expect to work on: \n\nNative iOS experiences optimized for mobile contexts and on-the-go usage\nAudio and voice interface components that leverage iOS platform capabilities\nReal-time communication and media processing features\nSeamless integration with our backend AI agent systems \nOur data infrastructure processes millions of media articles, social posts, and stakeholder signals daily. Our agents don't just answer questions—they generate press releases, analyze media coverage, and provide strategic recommendations. Your mobile work will make these capabilities accessible in new contexts where desktop access isn't practical. \n\nResponsibilities \n\nDesign and implement native iOS applications using Swift for internal enterprise deployment\nBuild features leveraging iOS frameworks for audio, media, and real-time communication\nIntegrate with backend APIs and services built by our platform engineering team\nOwn iOS app architecture, performance optimization, and code quality\nManage enterprise app distribution and deployment workflows\nCollaborate with backend engineers on API design and integration patterns\nEnsure security and compliance requirements for enterprise mobile applications\nBalance feature development with technical excellence—building for the long term while shipping quickly \nQualifications \n\nRequired: \n\n4+ years of professional iOS development experience with Swift\nStrong expertise in iOS frameworks, particularly AVFoundation and related audio/media APIs\nExperience building and deploying enterprise iOS applications\nSolid understanding of iOS app architecture, performance optimization, and memory management\nExperience integrating mobile apps with REST APIs and real-time protocols\nFamiliarity with enterprise app distribution (Apple Business Manager, MDM, TestFlight)\nAbility to work independently and make architectural decisions\nTrack record of shipping high-quality iOS apps to production \nNice to Have: \n\nExperience with Core ML or on-device machine learning\nBackground in real-time audio/video applications or communication tools\nExperience with WebRTC or streaming protocols\nInterest in voice interfaces and conversational UI design\nExperience with enterprise security and compliance requirements\nFamiliarity with TypeScript/Node.js ecosystems\nBackground working in fast-paced startup or innovation lab environments \nWhat We Offer \n\nOwnership of iOS development for a production AI platform used across the firm\nAutonomy to make technical decisions and shape mobile architecture from the ground up\nWork on real technical challenges that directly impact how consultants work\nCollaborative environment with talented engineers, data scientists, and AI researchers\nOpportunity to learn how AI agent systems work in enterprise environments\nCompetitive compensation and benefits\nRemote-friendly culture with flexibility \nWhy This Role Matters \n\nYou'll be building the foundation for how professionals interact with AI on mobile devices. This isn't a side project—it's a strategic expansion of capabilities that consultants already depend on. Your work will enable AI assistance in contexts where it matters most: when consultants are on the go, in meetings, or need hands-free access to intelligent support. \n\nWe're scaling proven technology, not experimenting. The platform you'll extend is already delivering value daily. Your mobile work will make that value accessible in entirely new ways. \n\nAbout FGS Labs \n\nFGS Labs is FGS Global's innovation engine, building AI and data capabilities that are already in production and delivering value across the firm. Our flagship platform, Fergus, is a live AI assistant used daily by consultants worldwide, powered by real-time media intelligence, proprietary data sources, and specialized agents for M&A, crisis communications, and stakeholder strategy. \n\nAbout FGS Global\n\nFGS Global is the world’s leading stakeholder strategy firm, with over 1,500 professionals around the world, advising clients in navigating critical issues and reputational challenges. FGS was formed from the combination of Finsbury, The Glover Park Group, Hering Schuppener and Sard Verbinnen & Co to offer board-level and C-suite counsel in all aspects of stakeholder strategy — including corporate reputation, crisis management, and public affairs and is also the leading force in transaction and financial communications worldwide.\n\nFGS offers seamless and integrated support with offices in the following locations: Abu Dhabi, Amsterdam, Beijing, Berlin, Boston, Brussels, Calgary, Chicago, Dubai, Dublin, Düsseldorf, Frankfurt, Hong Kong, Houston, Kingston, London, Los Angeles, Munich, Paris, Riyadh, San Francisco, Shanghai, Singapore, South Florida, The Hague, Tokyo, Toronto, Vancouver, Washington, D.C., and Zurich. The firm is headquartered in New York.\n\nFGS is consistently ranked a Band 1 PR firm for Crisis & Risk Management and for Litigation Support by Chambers and Partners.  For the second year, FGS was ranked #1 Global M&A PR firm by Deal Count and Value in 2024 by Mergermarket.\n\n \n\nWe are looking to fill this position as quickly as possible and are open to both freelance and permanent employment arrangements. \n\nFGS Global is committed to creating a diverse and inclusive environment and welcomes applicants from all backgrounds. \n\nNew York City Salary Range\n$100,000—$140,000 USD",
