      "Full Stack Developer - React / Node.js\nHello Innovation\nDetroit, MI • Remote\n\n\n1-Click Apply\n\n\nFull-time\n\nMedical, Dental, Retirement\n\nPosted 7 days ago\n\nJob description\n \nWe are open to remote candidates but we’d love for you to join us in Detroit, Pontiac or Porto Alegre, Brazil.\n\nCode, create, innovate, and solve never-been-done-before problems. \n\nAs a Full Stack Developer, you’ll be our go-to for making the impossible possible. If disrupting markets and shifting culture with products the world has never seen before doesn’t scare you, then keep reading.\n\nAbout Us\nAt Hello Innovation, we're more than just a company; we're a force for change. As the parent company to an ever-growing portfolio of businesses, we’re making the world a radically better place through meaningful innovation.\n\nHere, it's not about the daily grind; it's about making a real difference, challenging the norm, breaking boundaries, and rewriting what's possible.\n\nWe started from scratch—no investors, no debt—just a relentless drive that has led us to impact over a billion lives through our products. And we’re just getting started.  \n\nWe’re an eclectic team of dreamers, creators and doers, united in our mission to deliver work that truly matters. If you’re looking to be inspired, challenged and leave work every day knowing you did the best work of your life, you’ve come to the right place.\n \n\nAbout the Job\nAs a Full Stack Developer at Hello Innovation, you'll be at the forefront of creating cutting-edge web solutions that disrupt industries and improve the lives of tens of millions every month. \n\nUtilizing our modern tech stack, including React.js, Next.js, Node.js, NestJS, GraphQL, and PostgreSQL, you'll craft dynamic, responsive applications that redefine user experiences. \n\nIf you’re ready to craft the engines that drive the next big web application and work with a team that’s obsessed with delivering the best…then this job’s for you.\n \n\nAbout You\n\nYou’re a tech maestro. With expert knowledge in React.js and Next.js, you create engaging front-end experiences. Your  Node.js, NestJS and GraphQL prowess enable you to build scalable, robust backend services and efficient data-fetching APIs.\n \nGraphQL guru. You design and implement efficient, flexible APIs using GraphQL, enhancing data interaction and manipulation.\n \nStyling specialist. Proficient in CSS Modules, you ensure modular and reusable code. Your experience with Storybook and Radix aids in developing consistent, scalable UI components.\n \nWeb fundamentals. You're well-versed in HTML, CSS, and TypeScript, laying the foundation for robust web application development.\n \nDatabase savvy. You're experienced with PostgreSQL, designing schemas that support fast, reliable access to data.\n \nTesting is second nature. You understand the importance of testing, and are proficient in unit and integration testing to ensure your code is reliable and robust.\n \nYou’re a Git guru. Version control with Git is part of your daily workflow, ensuring collaborative and iterative development.\n \nContainerization is your ally. Experience with Docker helps you maintain consistency across development, testing, and production environments.\n \nYou’re up for the challenge. When others want to run for the hills, you want to dive deeper. Pushing the boundaries of web platforms, databases and cloud computing keeps you up at night.  \n \nYou get sh*t done. You’ve worked with small, scrappy teams and aren’t afraid to roll up your sleeves to get the job done -- no babysitter required.\n \nYou’re a systems thinker. You have the ability to see the big picture, zoom into the details and understand how all of the pieces work together. Your natural knack for connecting the dots helps you integrate complex systems.\n \nYou’re human-centered to the core. You truly understand people and are fueled by engaging with others to improve web app design, implementation and UI.\n \nIf your code took corporeal form, it would be a Ninja. Your work scales effortlessly from 100 connections to 100,000, responding so quickly that our customers forget they are even using the web. \n \nRefactoring is a religion, not a chore. You build solutions to the highest standards of coding and integrity and obsess over Unit Tests and Code Coverage. \n \nYou’re a modern-day MacGyver. You’ve never met a problem that couldn’t be solved.\n \nYou can’t stop thinking about what’s next. You’re passionate about implementing the latest frameworks, interacting with the latest APIs.\n \nThis isn’t your first rodeo. With 5+ years in the field, you've mastered our stack, particularly React and Node.js; demonstrating your ability to deliver complex projects from conception to production.\nYour Responsibilities \n\nCollaborate with the project stakeholders to understand the project requirements and objectives.\nDevelop full-stack web applications that are scalable, responsive, and user-centric, using our tech stack.\nEnsure code quality and maintainability by implementing best practices, including thorough testing and code reviews.\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams to define, design, and ship new features.\nMonitor and maintain the web app, ensuring that it is up-to-date and secure.\nStay ahead of the curve, continuously learning and applying the latest technologies and best practices to keep our stack modern and efficient.\nCompensation & Perks\n\nMeaningful work. This is not just a job. You can find a job anywhere. This is a place for the bold to get paid to give a sh*t and make a real impact on people’s lives when they need it most. \nBe part of something (really) big. Our products touch over 45 million people every month, and we are chasing problems that billions suffer from. Not just any problem, the ones that are filled with purpose and meaning. This is your chance to be more than a number and make history.\nDon’t just imagine it - create it at our Moonshot Factory. You’ll have access to our newly built Dreamlab, our secret research and development lab where employees aren’t focused on what’s today - but what’s next… Imagine a 30,000 sq ft facility with the machines, tools, and resources (from 7 axis robots to coating systems) to create…anything.\nNo red tape. Say goodbye to pointless meetings or political hoops to jump through. We’re scrappy, believe in autonomy and empower our teams to do whatever it takes to do the unthinkable. \nLearning animal environment. Learn more here than any other place on earth. We make sure you never stop growing and offer an allowance for continued learning. \nWe ignite the best in you. We exist not only to deliver meaningful innovation, but to ignite and inspire the creative problem solver in you.\nA creative, come-as-you-are environment. Our team never stops pushing you to be the best that you can be and still makes time to have some fun.\nTop of market pay. Along with a full benefits package including health, dental and 401k. \nPlus many more. Additional perks include daily catered lunches, team activities, paid holidays, bonuses and much more.\nDiversity isn’t just a checkbox. At Hello Innovation, our eclectic team from all walks of life is our secret sauce to meaningful innovation. Needless to say, we are an equal opportunity employer and do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.\n\nPowered by JazzHR\n\nMXarahPlA8",
